modules.description: This module provides operations to build and manipulate document templates through primitive elements (e.g., separators, whitespace), value conversions (integers, strings, etc.), and combinators for structuring content (wrapping, indenting, appending). It works with two core types: template values representing formatted output structures, and compiled template handles that support incremental updates with named values. The design enables use cases like pretty-printing nested data, generating structured text files (e.g., code, configs), and dynamically assembling documents with placeholders for later resolution.
